{"key":"post-9201411","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9201411</id>\n<content>You're going to want to inoculate your jars of rice grain first, and then when they're fully colonized, use them to inoculate your straw/hemp fibers.&amp;nbsp; Don't try to skip that step or it will all turn to green mold on you before you get your first flush.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you can't find perlite, you'll get higher humidity by placing paper or cloth towels in the bottom and keeping them damp,&amp;nbsp; not wet.&amp;nbsp; The towels will increase the surface area of water being evaporated into your fruiting chamber.&amp;nbsp; Be sure to replace them every few days with clean ones to prevent mold.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9201438</next>\n<prev>9201270</prev>\n<first>9200615</first>\n<last>9211055</last>\n<when>1226080522</when>\n<utime>11/07/08 07:55 PM</utime>\n</post>"}